<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The Commission contemplates that an ethics training provider would be able to document that a registrant had undertaken
various steps required for the provider to verify completion. The provider would be required under revised paragraph
(b)(4) of Rule 3.34 to keep documentation to support its determination that ethics training has been properly completed
by a registrant and to support its issuance of a certificate of attendance.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=5 f=1 -->
25
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

