<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;15.12
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Filing of claims.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Who may file.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) A claim may be made pursuant to this subpart by an employee or by a spouse or authorized agent, or legal representative
on behalf of the employee. If the employee is deceased, the claim may be filed by a survivor in the following order of
preference: spouse, children, parent, brother or sister or the authorized agent or legal representative of such
person or persons.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) A claim may not be made hereunder by or for the benefit of a subrogee, assignee, conditional vendor or other third
party.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Where to file.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 A claim hereunder must be presented in writing. If the claimant's official duty station is at the Department's national
office in Washington, DC, or if the claim is for an amount in excess of $25,000, the claim should be filed with the Counsel
for Claims, Office of the Solicitor of Labor, U.S. Department of Labor, Suite S4325, 200 Constitution Avenue, NW.,
Washington, DC 20210. In all other cases the claimant shall address the claim to the regional or branch office of the
Solicitor of Labor servicing the claimant's official duty station.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Evidence required.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The claimant is responsible for substantiating ownership or possession, the facts surrounding the loss or damage,
and the value of the property. Any claim filed hereunder must be accompanied by the following:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) A written statement, signed by the claimant or his or her authorized agent, setting forth the circumstances under
which the damage or loss occurred. This statement shall also include:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) A description of the type, design, model number or other identification of the property.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The date of purchase or acquisition and the original cost of the property.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) The location of the property when the loss or damage occurred.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) The value of the property when lost or damaged.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) The actual or estimated cost of the repair of any damaged item.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vi) The purpose of and authority for travel, if the loss or damage occurred incident to transportation or to the use
of a motor vehicle.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vii) Any and all available information as to the party responsible for the loss or damage, if such party is someone
other than the claimant, and all information as to insurance contracts, whether held by the claimant or by the party
responsible.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Copies of all available and appropriate documents such as bills of sale, estimates of repairs, or travel orders.
In the case of an automobile, the claimant must file two estimates of repair or a certified paid bill showing the damage
incurred and the cost of all parts, labor and other items necessary to the repair of the vehicle or a statement from an
authorized dealer or repair garage showing that the cost of such repairs exceeds the value of the vehicle.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) A copy of the power of attorney or other authorization if the claim is filed by someone other than the employee.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) A statement from the employee's immediate supervisor confirming that possession of the property was reasonable,
useful or proper under the circumstances and that the damage or loss was incident to service.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Time limitations.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 A claim under this part may be allowed only if it is filed in writing within 2 years after accrual of the claim. For the
purpose of this part, a claim accrues at the later of:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) the time of the accident or incident causing the loss or damage,
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) such time as the loss or damage should have been discovered by the claimant by the exercise of due diligence or
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) such time as cause preventing filing no longer exists or as war or armed conflict ends, whichever is earlier, if
a claim otherwise accrues during war or an armed conflict or has accrued within two years before war or an armed conflict
begins, and for cause shown.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;15.13
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Allowable claims.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) A claim may be allowed only if the property involved was being used incident to service with the Department and:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The damage or loss was not caused wholly or partly by the negligent or wrongful act or omission of the claimant, his
or her agent, the members of his or her family, or his or her private employee (the standard to be applied is that of reasonable
care under the circumstances); and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The possession of the property lost or damaged and the quantity and the quality possessed is determined to have
been reasonable, useful or proper under the circumstances; and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The claim is substantiated by proper and convincing evidence.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940722-1-00033 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940722-1-00011 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(b) Claims which are otherwise allowable under this subpart shall not be disallowed solely because the claimant was
not the legal owner of the property for which the claim is made.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) Subject to the conditions in paragraph (a) of this section and the other provisions of this subpart, any claim for
damage to, or loss, of personal property incident to service with the Department may be considered and allowed. For
the purpose of subpart B of this part, an alternative work location at which an employee is performing duties pursuant
to an approved Flexiplace agreement shall be considered an official duty station. The following are examples of the
principal types of claims which may be allowed, but these examples are not exclusive and other types of claims may be
allowed, unless hereinafter excluded:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Property or damage in quarters or other authorized places.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Claims may be allowable for damage to, or loss of, property arising from fire, flood, hurricane, other natural disaster,
theft, or other unusual occurrence, while such property is located at:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Quarters within the 50 States or the District of Columbia that were assigned to the claimant or otherwise provided
in kind by the United States; or
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Quarters outside the 50 States and the District of Columbia that were occupied by the claimant, whether or not
they were assigned or otherwise provided in kind by the United States, except when the claimant is a civilian employee
who is a local inhabitant; or
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Any warehouse, office, working area or other place (except quarters) authorized or apparently authorized
for the reception or storage of property.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Transportation or travel losses.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Claims may be allowed for damage to, or loss of, property incident to transportation or storage pursuant to order or
in connection with travel under orders, including property in the custody of a carrier, an agent or agency of the Government,
or the claimant.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Mobile homes.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Claims may be allowed for damage to, or loss of, mobile homes and their contents under the provisions of paragraph (c)(2)
of this section. Claims for structural damage to mobile homes, other than that caused by collision, and damage to contents
of mobile homes resulting from such structural damage, must contain conclusive evidence that the damage was not caused
by structural deficiency of the mobile home and that it was not overloaded. Claims for damage to, or loss of, tires mounted
on mobile homes will not be allowed, except in cases of collision, theft or vandalism.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Enemy action or public service.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Claims may be allowed for damage to, or loss of, property as a direct consequence of:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Enemy action or threat thereof, or combat, guerilla, brigandage, or other belligerent activity, or unjust confiscation
by a foreign power or its nationals.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Action by the claimant to quiet a civil disturbance or to alleviate a public disaster.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Efforts by the claimant to save human life or Government property.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Property used for the benefit of the Government.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Claims may be allowed for damage to, or loss, of property when used for the benefit of the Government at the request of,
or with the knowledge and consent of superior authority.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Clothing and accessories.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Claims may be allowed for damage to, or loss, of property when used for damage to or loss of, clothing and accessories
customarily worn on the person, such as eyeglasses, hearing aids, or dentures.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Expenses incident to repair.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Claimants may be reimbursed for the payment of any sales tax incurred in connection with repairs to an item. The costs
of obtaining estimates of repair (subject to the limitations set forth in &sect;15.14(c)) are also allowable.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;15.14 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Restrictions on certain claims.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
