<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940722-1-00036 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940722-1-00011 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) When the amount recovered from a carrier, insurer, or other third party is greater than or equal to the claimant's
total loss as determined under this part, no compensation is allowable under this subpart.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) When the amount recovered is less than such total loss, the allowable amount is determined by deducting the recovery
from the amount of such total loss.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) For this purpose, the claimant's total loss is to be determined without regard to the maximum payment limitations
set forth in &sect;15.11.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
However, if the resulting amount, after making this deduction, exceeds the maximum payment limitations, the claimant
shall be allowed only the maximum amount set forth in &sect;15.11.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;15.17 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Claims procedures.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Award.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The Counsel for Claims, the Regional Solicitors, and the Associate Regional Solicitors are authorized to consider,
ascertain, adjust, determine, compromise and settle claims filed under this subpart that arose within their respective
jurisdictions, except that any claim for an amount in excess of $25,000 shall fall within the exclusive jurisdiction
of the Counsel for Claims.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Form of claim.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Any writing received by the Office of the Solicitor within the time limits set forth in &sect;15.12(d) will be accepted
and considered a claim under the Act if it constitutes a demand for compensation from the Department. A demand is not
required to be for a specific sum of money.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Notification.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The determination upon the claim shall be provided to the claimant in writing by the deciding official.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;15.18 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Computation of award and finality of settlement.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) The amount allowable for damage to or loss of any item of property may not exceed the lowest of
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The amount requested by the claimant for the item as a result of its loss, damage or the cost of its repair, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The actual or estimated cost of its repair, or
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The actual value at the time of its loss, damage, or destruction. The actual value is determined by using the current
replacement cost or the depreciated value of the item since its acquisition, whichever is lower, less any salvage
value of the item in question.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Depreciation in value is determined by considering the type of article involved, its cost, its condition when
damaged or lost, and the time elapsed between the date of acquisition and the date of damage or loss.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) Current replacement cost and depreciated value are determined by use of publicly available adjustment rates
or through use of other reasonable methods at the discretion of the official authorized to issue a determination upon
the claim in question.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) Replacement of lost or damaged property may be made in kind wherever appropriate.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
