minimum ones required. Also, &sect;23.1303(d) would add a requirement for those airplanes whose performance must
be based on weight, altitude, and temperature to be equipped with a free air temperature indicator. A new sentence
added to &sect;23.1303(e)(2) would state that nuisance overspeed warnings should not occur at lower speeds where
pilots might ignore the warning. A new paragraph (f) would propose requirements for attitude instruments that include
