<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Has lighted position lights; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Is in an area that is marked by obstruction lights;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Anchor an aircraft unless the aircraft_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Has lighted anchor lights; or
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Is in an area where anchor lights are not required on vessels; or
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Operate an aircraft that is equipped with an anticollision light system, unless it has lighted anticollision
lights. However, the anticollision lights need not be lighted when the pilot-in-command determines that, because
of operating conditions, it would be in the interest of safety to turn the lights off.
